Title: Grand Canyon Easter Services
Description_y: Easter services at the Grand Canyon, including commentary by Governor Pyle, services by Rev. Thomas Miller Pyle (Buckeye, Arizona) and Shrine of the Ages Pastor Rev. Kenneth Porray, and music by the Shrine of the Ages Boys Choir and Arizona State College Flagstaff.
Geographic Subject: Shrine of the Ages Chapel (Grand Canyon, Ariz.)
Geographic Subjects: Shrine of the Ages Chapel (Grand Canyon, Ariz.)

Title: United Nations Conference, San Francisco
Description_y: This recording includes interviews with NBC's Frank McCall regarding technical difficulties associated with broadcasting and organizing the conference and with Carveth Wells, NBC radio announcer Ben Grauer, and John Wald of Richfield Reporters regarding conference proceedings.  Also included are greetings from Arizonans Capt. and Mrs. Joseph Madison Greer, who were stationed at the Merritt Island Navy Yard and Hospital.
Corporate Name Subject: United Nations Conference on International Organization (1945 : San Francisco, Calif.)|http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n82058955
Contributors-Person: Pyle, Howard, 1906-1987|http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n93045685|Interviewer||Grauer, Ben|http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n85301300|Interviewee||Wald, John, 1908-1988|Interviewee||McCall, Francis Cleaves, 1907-1981|Interviewee||Wells, Carveth|http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n88278008|Interviewee||Greer, Joseph Madison, 1887-1969|Interviewee||Greer, Mary Susan Rasmusson, 1889-1957|Interviewee

Title: General Douglas MacArthur Speech
Description_y: Address by General Douglas MacArthur at the Special Session of the 1st Congress of the Philippines with Pyle's reporting.

Title: "What is Right for America?"
Description_y: Howard Pyle delivered this speech, which discusses the "vanishing American" and references Herbert Hoover, at the 1952 Republican National Convention.

Item Title: Track 05: GHQ Hometowners Prog. 265-3, July 28, 1945
Subjects: World War, 1939-1945. || Phillipines -- History -- 1898-1946. || United States. Army. Division, 32nd.
Description_x:
“Broadcast #3 in new series for KTAR”. Interviews with soldiers from 32nd
Division” at Luzon, Philippines: James Burchett, Eloy AZ; Faustino Estrada,
Williams AZ; Billy J. Hill, Miami AZ; Homer Cummings, Jerome AZ.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: GHQ Hometowners Program
Description_y: Pyle interviews James Burchett (Eloy, Arizona), Faustino Estrada (Williams, Arizona), Billy J. Hill (Miami, Arizona), and Homer Cummings (Jerome, Arizona) who are stationed in Luzon, Philippines with the 32nd Division.  This broadcast is the third of KTAR's Hometowner series.

Item Title: Track 06: GHQ Hometowners Prog. 265-4, July 28, 1945.
Subjects: World War, 1939-1945. || African Americans. || United States. Army. Aviation Engineers, 856th.
Description_x: “Broadcast #4 in new series for KTAR” Interviews with African-American soldiers from “856th Aviation Engineers” near Manila, Philippines: Edward E. Davis, Scottsdale AZ; Robert Foley, Tucson AZ; Sylvester Ware, Phoenix; Willie Hill, Tucson
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: GHQ Hometowners Program
Description_y: Pyle interviews Edward E. Davis (Scottsdale, Arizona), Robert Foley (Tucson, Arizona), Sylvester Ware (Phoenix, Arizona), and Willie Hill (Tucson, Arizona) who are stationed in Manila, Philippines with the 856th Aviation Engineers.  This broadcast is the fourth of KTAR's Hometowner series.
Topical Subjects: World War, 1939-1945 -- Personal narratives, American||World War, 1939-1945 -- Participation, African-American

Item Title: Track 08: J. H. Pyle reports from Yokohama, September 1, 1945.
Description_x: Describes flight to and arrival at Yokohama, Japan with 11th Airborne Division. Claims 1st civilian US broadcaster to land at Japan, met 4th Marine Division, describes drive to Radio Tokyo.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: J. Howard Pyle Reports from Yokohama
Description_y: Pyle describes his flight to and arrival at Yokohama, Japan with 11th Airborne Division.  He also claims to be the first civilian US broadcaster to land in Japan, meets the 4th Marine Division, and describes the drive to Radio Tokyo.

Item Title: Track 09: Governor Pyle Reports on Meeting with Tribal Leaders, September 24, 1951.
Subjects: Indians of North America -- Arizona -- Politics and Government.
Description_x: Interviews with George Fisher, Colorado River Tribal Council; Clarence Wesley, San Carlos Tribal Council; Sam Ahkeah, Navajo Tribal Council; Thomas Segundo, Papago Tribal Council. [Possible origin of the Inter Tribal Council of Arizona] KOY Broadcast.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: Governor Pyle Reports on Meeting with Tribal Leaders
Description_y: Pyle interviews George Fisher (Colorado River Tribal Council), Clarence Wesley (San Carlos Tribal Council), Sam Ahkeah (Navajo Tribal Council), and Thomas Segundo (Papago Tribal Council). This gathering may represent the origin of the Inter-Tribal Council of Arizona.

Item Title: Track 10: Grand Canyon Easter Services Part 2, March 25, 1951.
Description_x: Governor Pyle, Rev. Thomas Miller Pyle of Buckeye AZ, Rev. Kenneth Poray (sp?), Pastor at Grand Canyon, Music of the Shrine of the Ages Boys Choir, Arizona State College Flagstaff. KTAR broadcast.

Item Title: Track 11: Grand Canyon Easter Services Part 1, March 25, 1951.
Description_x: Governor Pyle, Rev. Thomas Miller Pyle of Buckeye AZ, Rev. Kenneth Poray (sp?), Pastor at Grand Canyon, Music of the Shrine of the Ages Boys Choir, Arizona State College Flagstaff. KTAR broadcast.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: Grand Canyon Easter Services (Part 1)
Description_y: Easter services at the Grand Canyon, including commentary by Governor Pyle, services by Rev. Thomas Miller Pyle (Buckeye, Arizona) and Shrine of the Ages Pastor Rev. Kenneth Porray, and music by the Shrine of the Ages Boys Choir and Arizona State College Flagstaff.

Item Title: Track 13:  GHQ Valley Bank #3044 [GI Bill of Rights, the Bloody Path, Hometowner Interviews]
Subjects: United States. Montgomery G.I. Bill. || United States. Army. Infantry Division, 25th. || Luzon (Philippines) -- History, Military. || World War, 1939-1945.
Description_x: Fred MacPherson commentary re: GI Bill of Rights. J. H. Pyle report from 25th Division, interviews with: Lt. Kenneth J. Fuller, Mesa AZ; Lt. Hiram H. Zupnik, Tucson AZ re: battle in Luzon, in particular the “Bloody Path” skirmish. The officers describe divisional operations & decisions made. Enlisted men describe Army life in the battle zones; Greeting from Lt. Arnold Ambos of Globe AZ. September 4, 1945.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: GHQ Hometowners Program
Description_y: This recording includes Fred MacPherson's commentary on the GI Bill of Rights, J. Howard Pyle reporting from the 25th Division, and interviews with Lt. Kenneth J. Fuller (Mesa, Arizona) and Lt. Hiram H. Zupnik (Tucson, Arizona) regarding the battle in Luzon and specifically the “Bloody Path” skirmish. Fuller and Zupnik describe divisional operations and the decisions made while enlisted men recount Army life in the battle zones.  Also included is a greeting from Lt. Arnold Ambos (Globe, Arizona).
Topical Subjects: United States. Montgomery G.I. Bill||World War, 1939-1945 -- Campaigns -- Philippines -- Luzon

Item Title: Track 14: United Nations Conference San Francisco Part 2. #2655, April 29, 1945
Subjects: United Nations -- History. || United Nations Conference on International Organization (1945 : San Francisco, Calif.)
Description_x: Includes interviews with Frank McCall, NBC re: technical difficulties with broadcast and organizing conference; Carveth Wells re: conference proceedings; Greetings from Capt. and Mrs. Joseph Madison Greer, Arizonans stationed at Merritt Island Navy Yard and Hospital.
Series_x: United Nations Conference on International Organization
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: United Nations Conference, San Francisco (Part 2)
Description_y: Interviews with NBC's Frank McCall regarding technical difficulties associated with broadcasting and organizing the conference and with Carveth Wells regarding conference proceedings.  Also included are greetings from Arizonans Capt. and Mrs. Joseph Madison Greer, who were stationed at the Merritt Island Navy Yard and Hospital.

Item Title: Track 23: Interview with K. A. Piersson
Description_x: Describes his perceptions and experiences with Japanese occupation of Manila, prospects for the future of the Phillipines, and the qualities of the American soldier.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: Interview with K. A. Piersson
Description_y: Piersson recounts his perceptions and experiences during the Japanese occupation of Manila, speculates on prospects for the future of the Philippines, and describes the qualities of the American soldier.

Item Title: Track 25: Interviews with Arizona Army nurses, August 9, 1945
Subjects: World War, 1939-1945 -- Medical Care. || Military Nursing.
Description_x:
Interviews with Lt. Laura Celaya of Tempe, 120th General Hospital; Lt. Mary Ellen Smith of
Buckeye, 80th General Hospital. Addition to 158th Infantry series.

Item Title: Track 26: Interviews with Arizona Army nurses, August 9, 1945
Subjects: World War, 1939-1945 -- Medical Care. || Military Nursing.
Description_x: Interviews with Lt. Agnes Mitchell of Chinle, 80th General Hospital; Lt. Doris Norberg of Warren, 313th General Hospital. She met her fiancee at Fort Huachuca. Addition to 158th Infantry series.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: Interviews with Arizona Army Nurses
Description_y: Pyle interviews Lt. Agnes Mitchell (Chinle, Arizona) of the 80th General Hospital and Lt. Doris Norberg (Warren, Arizona) of the 313th General Hospital.  Norberg met her fiance at Fort Huachuca.

Item Title: Track 27: GHQ SWPA Hometowners Recordings for KTAR August 4, 1945
Description_x: Interviews with Manuel Marino Caballeros of Patagonia; Lt. John P. Diaz of Phoenix (1942 ASC graduate); Pyle summarizes and wraps up the 158th Infantry series. Broadcast #9, 158th Regimental Combat Team series.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: GHQ Hometowners Program
Description_y: Pyle interviews Manuel Moreno Caballeros (Patagonia, Arizona) and Lt. John P. Diaz (Phoenix, Arizona).  Diaz graduated from Arizona State College in 1942.  Pyle also summarizes and wraps up the 158th Infantry series.  This recording is broadcast #9 in the 158th Regimental Combat Team series.
Topical Subjects: World War, 1939-1945 -- Participation, Mexican American||World War, 1939-1945 -- Personal narratives, American

Item Title: Track 28: GHQ SWPA Hometowners Recordings for KTAR, n.d.
Subjects: World War, 1939-1945. || United States. Army. Infantry Regiment, 158th -- History. || Mexican Americans.
Description_x: Interviews with Rudolph Caballeros of Benson AZ; Leon J. Gailey, Litchfield Park; Raul L. Vasquez, Tempe AZ; Captain Marquez Gawinner, Atlanta Georgia re: Arizona Bushmasters. Broadcast #7, 158th Regimental Combat Team series from Legaspi area of southern Luzon.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: GHQ Hometowners Program
Description_y: Pyle interviews Rudolph Caballero (Benson, Arizona), Leon G. Gailey (Litchfield Park, Arizona), Raul L. Vasquez (Tempe, Arizona), and Captain Marcus N. Gewinner (Atlanta, Georgia) regarding the Arizona Bushmasters.  This broadcast is #7 in the 158th Regimental Combat Team series and was made from the Legaspi area of southern Luzon.
Topical Subjects: World War, 1939-1945 -- Participation, Mexican American||World War, 1939-1945 -- Personal narratives, American

Item Title: Track 30: GHQ SWPA Hometowners Recordings for KTAR, n.d.
Subjects: World War, 1939-1945. || Mexican Americans. || United States. Army. Infantry Regiment, 158th -- History.
Description_x: Interviews with soldiers of the 2nd Battalion: Manuel Morales of Tucson; Charles H. Lovett of Coolidge; Emmanuel Bustamante of Tempe; Leonardo Hernandez of Nogales. Broadcast #6, 158th Regimental Combat Team series from Noga, southern Luzon.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: GHQ Hometowners Program
Description_y: Pyle interviews Manuel Morales (Tucson, Arizona), Charles H. Lovett (Coolidge, Arizona), Emmanuel Bustamante (Tempe, Arizona), and Leonardo Hernandez (Nogales, Arizona).  These soldiers were part of the 2nd Battalion of the 158th Regimental Combat Team.  This broadcast is #6 in the 158th Regimental Combat Team series and was made from Noga in southern Luzon.
Topical Subjects: World War, 1939-1945 -- Participation, Mexican American||World War, 1939-1945 -- Personal narratives, American

Item Title: Track 31: GHQ SWPA Hometowners Recordings for KTAR, n.d.
Subjects: World War, 1939-1945. || United States. Army. Infantry Regiment, 158th -- History.
Description_x: On rifle range w/Lt. Horace Damon of Glasgow Montana. Describes practice firing routine for 50mm anti-tank guns. Broadcast #5, 158th Regimental Combat Team series.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Title: GHQ Hometowners Program
Description_y: Pyle interviews Lt. Horace Damon (Glasgow, Montana) on the rifle range.  Damon describes the practice firing routine for 50mm anti-tank guns.  This broadcast is #5 in the 158th Regimental Combat Team series.

Item Title: General Yamashita Surrender Ceremony
Description_x: Howard Pyle's radio broadcast of the surrender ceremony at Baguio City, Philippines on September 2, 1945. Known as the "Tiger of Malaya", Yamashita surrendered in the presence of Generals Jonathan Wainwright and Arthur Percival, who were previously imprisoned by the Japanese  in Manchuria. Pyle said he was the only news correspondent to cover the Japanese surrender on board the USS Missouri and Yamashita's surrender at Baguio City.
Citation: Howard Pyle Collection (1883-1987). MSS-97. Greater Arizona Collection. ASU Library, Arizona State University, Tempe, AZ. http://azarchivesonline.org/xtf/view?docId=ead/asu/pyle.xml
Notes: Fair audio quality. Digitized from the original transcription disc in December 2015 with the support of the Luhrs Family Endowment.

Title: General Yamashita Surrender Ceremony (Side 1)
Description_y: Howard Pyle's radio broadcast of the surrender ceremony at Baguio City, Philippines. Known as the "Tiger of Malaya," Yamashita surrendered in the presence of Generals Jonathan Wainwright and Arthur Percival, who were previously imprisoned by the Japanese in Manchuria. Pyle said he was the only news correspondent to cover the Japanese surrender on board the USS Missouri and Yamashita's surrender at Baguio City.
